%% Evidence: docs/default_workflow.md, adl/src/control_plane.rs, docs/architecture/ADL_ARCHITECTURE.md
%% Assumptions: merge and closeout are human/governance events; tool state labels represent lifecycle checkpoints, not internal Rust enum names.
stateDiagram-v2
  [*] --> IssueCaptured
  IssueCaptured --> BundleInitialized: pr init
  BundleInitialized --> DoctorReady: pr ready
  DoctorReady --> WorktreeBound: pr run
  WorktreeBound --> Editing: implementation in worktree
  Editing --> ValidationChecked: focused doc checks pass
  ValidationChecked --> DraftPR: pr finish
  DraftPR --> ChecksPending: janitor monitors checks and reviews
  ChecksPending --> MergeGate: checks/review pass
  MergeGate --> MergeGate: rebase/refresh if needed
  ChecksPending --> RepairLoop: PR conflicts or review request
  RepairLoop --> Editing: bound edits and re-run validation
  MergeGate --> Merged: merged by human
  Merged --> ClosedOut: pr closeout
  ClosedOut --> [*]
